\v 10 \w They|strong="H3588"\w*\f + \fr 1:10 \ft God's enemies. \f* entangle \w themselves|strong="H4390"\w* \w like|strong="H5704"\w* people caught \w in|strong="H5518"\w* \w thorn|strong="H5518"\w* \w bushes|strong="H5518"\w*; \w they|strong="H3588"\w* \w are|strong="H4390"\w* \w like|strong="H5704"\w* drunks \w full|strong="H4390"\w* \w of|strong="H4390"\w* \w drink|strong="H5435"\w*. \w They|strong="H3588"\w* \w will|strong="H5704"\w* \w be|strong="H3588"\w* \w completely|strong="H5704"\w* burned \w up|strong="H5704"\w* \w like|strong="H5704"\w* \w dry|strong="H3002"\w* \w straw|strong="H7179"\w*.\f + \fr 1:10 \ft This verse is acknowledged as one of the hardest verses to translate in the Bible as the specific interpretation is uncertain. However, the main point of destruction of those opposed to God is clear.\f*
\v 11 \w One|strong="H4480"\w* \w of|strong="H3068"\w* \w you|strong="H5921"\w* \w is|strong="H3068"\w* plotting \w evil|strong="H7451"\w* \w against|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w Lord|strong="H3068"\w*, someone \w who|strong="H3068"\w* \w is|strong="H3068"\w* \w planning|strong="H2803"\w* \w wickedness|strong="H7451"\w*.
