\p 
\v 15 Look! \w A|strong="H3068"\w* messenger is coming over the mountains, bringing good news and proclaiming peace. Judah, celebrate your religious festivals and keep your vows, for never again will wicked enemies invade your land—they will be completely destroyed.
\b
\c 2
\p 
\v 1 \w The|strong="H3605"\w* \w one|strong="H3605"\w* \w who|strong="H3605"\w* scatters\f + \fr 2:1 \ft Or “smashes to pieces.”\f* \w has|strong="H3063"\w* \w come|strong="H5674"\w* \w to|strong="H5921"\w* attack \w you|strong="H3588"\w*! Guard \w the|strong="H3605"\w* fortresses! \w Watch|strong="H2009"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* roads! Get \w yourselves|strong="H5921"\w* ready! \w Call|strong="H8085"\w* \w every|strong="H3605"\w* soldier \w out|strong="H5921"\w*!
\p 
\v 2 (\w For|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* Lord \w will|strong="H5341"\w* \w restore|strong="H5927"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* splendor \w of|strong="H6440"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* people \w of|strong="H6440"\w* Jacob \w as|strong="H5927"\w* \w he|strong="H5921"\w* \w will|strong="H5341"\w* \w restore|strong="H5927"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* splendor \w of|strong="H6440"\w* Israel, \w for|strong="H5921"\w* invaders \w have|strong="H5921"\w* plundered \w them|strong="H5921"\w*, \w and|strong="H6440"\w* destroyed \w their|strong="H6440"\w* \w land|strong="H6440"\w*.\f + \fr 2:2 \ft Literally, “vine branches.”\f*)\f + \fr 2:2 \ft This sentence is placed in parentheses to indicate that it is not part of the description of the attacking army and its commander. \f*
\p 
\v 3 \w The|strong="H3588"\w* shields \w of|strong="H3068"\w* \w his|strong="H3068"\w* \w chief|strong="H3478"\w* soldiers \w are|strong="H3478"\w* red; \w the|strong="H3588"\w* warriors wear scarlet. \w His|strong="H3068"\w* chariots flash \w like|strong="H3478"\w* fire \w in|strong="H3478"\w* \w the|strong="H3588"\w* sunlight \w as|strong="H3068"\w* \w he|strong="H3588"\w* prepares \w for|strong="H3588"\w* battle. Spears \w with|strong="H3068"\w* \w their|strong="H3068"\w* wooden shafts\f + \fr 2:3 \ft The word for spear here is that of the wood used, and it is debated whether this is pine, cypress, or fir. \f* \w are|strong="H3478"\w* held \w up|strong="H7725"\w* \w and|strong="H3478"\w* shaken.
\v 4 \w Chariots|strong="H7393"\w* race madly through \w the|strong="H3117"\w* streets, rushing back \w and|strong="H3117"\w* \w forth|strong="H3559"\w* across \w the|strong="H3117"\w* town squares. Bright \w as|strong="H3117"\w* \w torches|strong="H6393"\w*, \w they|strong="H3117"\w* dash \w like|strong="H4043"\w* lightning flashes.
\v 5 \w He|strong="H2351"\w* shouts orders \w to|strong="H7323"\w* \w his|strong="H1984"\w* officers. \w They|strong="H7323"\w* stumble \w as|strong="H2351"\w* \w they|strong="H7323"\w* \w rush|strong="H8264"\w* \w to|strong="H7323"\w* attack \w the|strong="H1984"\w* wall. \w The|strong="H1984"\w* battering ram \w is|strong="H4758"\w* set up.
\v 6 \w The|strong="H2142"\w* river gates \w are|strong="H3782"\w* opened; \w the|strong="H2142"\w* palace washes away.\f + \fr 2:6 \ft Or “dissolves in fear.”\f*
\v 7 “Queen” Nineveh\f + \fr 2:7 \ft The word used here is of uncertain meaning. It does not occur anywhere else in the Old Testament. \f* \w is|strong="H8179"\w* stripped, \w and|strong="H8179"\w* led \w away|strong="H4127"\w* \w into|strong="H5104"\w* exile, \w with|strong="H4127"\w* \w her|strong="H6605"\w* servant girls mourning like doves, \w and|strong="H8179"\w* beating their breasts.
\v 8 \w Nineveh|strong="H5324"\w* \w is|strong="H6963"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* leaky pool—\w its|strong="H5921"\w* population \w is|strong="H6963"\w* \w like|strong="H5927"\w* water running \w away|strong="H1540"\w*. “Stop! Stop” people \w shout|strong="H6963"\w*, \w but|strong="H5921"\w* nobody \w turns|strong="H5921"\w* \w back|strong="H5927"\w*.
\v 9 Loot \w the|strong="H3117"\w* silver! Loot \w the|strong="H3117"\w* gold! \w There|strong="H1992"\w*'s an endless supply—an abundance \w of|strong="H3117"\w* everything \w you|strong="H3117"\w* could \w ever|strong="H3117"\w* want.
\v 10 Deserted, destroyed, devastated! Hearts faint, knees tremble, stomachs ache. \w Everyone|strong="H3605"\w*'s faces turn pale.
\p 
\v 11 Where now \w is|strong="H3820"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* lion's den? Where \w is|strong="H3820"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w place|strong="H3605"\w* where \w the|strong="H3605"\w* young lions \w used|strong="H3605"\w* \w to|strong="H3820"\w* feed? Where \w is|strong="H3820"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* lion, \w and|strong="H6440"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* lioness, \w and|strong="H6440"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* lion cub \w that|strong="H3605"\w* \w were|strong="H3820"\w* afraid \w of|strong="H6440"\w* \w no|strong="H3605"\w* \w one|strong="H3605"\w*?\f + \fr 2:11 \ft The symbol of the lion was used extensively by the Assyrians, and also reflects their cruel treatment of their victims.\f*
\v 12 \w The|strong="H8033"\w* \w lion|strong="H3715"\w* tears apart meat \w for|strong="H8033"\w* \w his|strong="H1980"\w* \w cubs|strong="H1482"\w*, \w and|strong="H1980"\w* strangles prey \w for|strong="H8033"\w* \w his|strong="H1980"\w* \w lionesses|strong="H3833"\w*. \w He|strong="H1931"\w* fills \w his|strong="H1980"\w* \w den|strong="H4583"\w* \w with|strong="H1980"\w* prey, \w his|strong="H1980"\w* lair \w with|strong="H1980"\w* carcasses.
\p 
\v 13 Watch out! \w For|strong="H4390"\w* \w I|strong="H1767"\w* am against \w you|strong="H1767"\w*, declares \w the|strong="H4390"\w* Lord Almighty. \w I|strong="H1767"\w* will \w set|strong="H4390"\w* fire \w to|strong="H1767"\w* \w your|strong="H4390"\w* chariots \w and|strong="H3833"\w* they will go up \w in|strong="H2963"\w* smoke. \w Your|strong="H4390"\w* strong \w young|strong="H3833"\w* men\f + \fr 2:13 \ft Literally, “young lions.”\f* will be \w killed|strong="H2614"\w* \w by|strong="H2966"\w* \w the|strong="H4390"\w* sword. \w I|strong="H1767"\w* will stop \w you|strong="H1767"\w* plundering other peoples.\f + \fr 2:13 \ft Literally, “cut off your prey from the earth.”\f* \w The|strong="H4390"\w* demands \w of|strong="H4390"\w* \w your|strong="H4390"\w* ambassadors\f + \fr 2:13 \ft Emissaries: the Assyrians sent their representatives to other nations to demand submission and tribute.\f* will no longer be heard.
\b
\c 3
\p 
\v 1 What \w a|strong="H3068"\w* disaster \w is|strong="H3605"\w* coming upon \w this|strong="H3605"\w* murderous \w city|strong="H5892"\w* \w with|strong="H5892"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w its|strong="H3605"\w* treachery! \w It|strong="H3808"\w* \w is|strong="H3605"\w* \w full|strong="H3605"\w* \w of|strong="H5892"\w* \w wealth|strong="H3808"\w* \w it|strong="H3808"\w* \w has|strong="H3605"\w* robbed, \w and|strong="H5892"\w* \w always|strong="H3605"\w* \w has|strong="H3605"\w* \w plenty|strong="H3605"\w* \w of|strong="H5892"\w* victims.\f + \fr 3:1 \ft Literally, “its prey never departs.”\f*
